{
  "page": "Courtesan",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Lady_Johanna,_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5b/Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png/350px-Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"467\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5b/Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png/525px-Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5b/Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png/700px-Lady_Johanna%2C_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Lady_Johanna,_the_Black_Swan_by_viscardiac.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Johanna_Swann\" title=\"Johanna Swann\">Black Swan</a>, by viscardiac ©</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Courtesan</b> is a profession which uses charm, refinement and <a href=\"/index.php/Gender_and_sexuality\" title=\"Gender and sexuality\">sexuality</a> to attract high status suitors, patrons and lovers. Though the term courtesan usually refer to women, male courtesans exist also.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> They are found in the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>, most notably <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters_-_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters_-_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Braavos\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Braavos</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Lys\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Lys</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#The_Winds_of_Winter\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>The Winds of Winter</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Famous_courtesans\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Famous courtesans</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Braavos\">Braavos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Braavos\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a> is renowned worldwide for its cultured courtesans who enjoy high status.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Every courtesan has her own barge and servants to work them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> They are showered with gifts from <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">goldsmiths</a>, and craftsmen beg for their custom. <a href=\"/index.php/Nobility\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nobility\">Nobility</a> and rich merchants pay the courtesans large amounts of money to appear alongside them at events, and <a href=\"/index.php/Bravo\" title=\"Bravo\">bravos</a> are known to kill each other in their names.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The courtesans of Braavos are all free women, with the most famous taking poetic names.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The beauty of famed courtesans has inspired many songs, and there are <a href=\"/index.php/Marble\" title=\"Marble\">marble</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bronze\" title=\"Bronze\">bronze</a> statues of some Braavosi courtesans.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Some families have produced many generations of courtesans, such as the descendants of <a href=\"/index.php/Bellegere_Otherys\" title=\"Bellegere Otherys\">Bellegere Otherys</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Lys\">Lys</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Lys\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The courtesans from the <a href=\"/index.php/Pleasure_gardens\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pleasure gardens\">pleasure gardens</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a> are famed for their beauty, but they are all <a href=\"/index.php/Slaves\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slaves\">slaves</a>, unlike the free women of Braavos.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The Lyseni breed their slaves to develop beautiful courtesans and bedslaves.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters_-_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters_-_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tyanna_of_the_Tower_by_Laura_Avellino.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/Tyanna_of_the_Tower_by_Laura_Avellino.jpg/350px-Tyanna_of_the_Tower_by_Laura_Avellino.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/Tyanna_of_the_Tower_by_Laura_Avellino.jpg/525px-Tyanna_of_the_Tower_by_Laura_Avellino.jpg 1.5x, /images/f/fe/Tyanna_of_the_Tower_by_Laura_Avellino.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tyanna_of_the_Tower_by_Laura_Avellino.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Tyanna_of_the_Tower\" title=\"Tyanna of the Tower\">Tyanna of the Tower</a>, by Laura Avellino ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Prior to becoming involved with <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor Targaryen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Tyanna_of_the_Tower\" title=\"Tyanna of the Tower\">Tyanna of the Tower</a> was a tavern dancer who became a courtesan in <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Courtesans across the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a> were among the informants whom Grand Master <a href=\"/index.php/Benifer\" title=\"Benifer\">Benifer</a> utilized during his search for the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon eggs</a> taken by <a href=\"/index.php/Elissa_Farman\" title=\"Elissa Farman\">Elissa Farman</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Known as the Black Swan, <a href=\"/index.php/Johanna_Swann\" title=\"Johanna Swann\">Johanna Swann</a> was a courtesan who rose to become ruler of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a> in all but name.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon:_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon:_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchy\" title=\"Triarchy\">Triarchy</a> fell into infighting after the murder of <a href=\"/index.php/Sharako_Lohar\" title=\"Sharako Lohar\">Sharako Lohar</a> by a rival for the affections of the Black Swan.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters_-_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters_-_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Part of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Manfryd_Mooton\" title=\"Manfryd Mooton\">Manfryd Mooton</a>'s mission to the <a href=\"/index.php/Sealord_of_Braavos\" title=\"Sealord of Braavos\">Sealord of Braavos</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Follard\" title=\"Lord Follard\">Lord Follard</a> chose to remain in <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a> because of a courtesan instead of returning to <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Lysandro_Rogare\" title=\"Lysandro Rogare\">Lysandro Rogare</a> is said to have contemplated having <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys II Targaryen\">Viserys Targaryen</a> work as a courtesan at the <a href=\"/index.php/Perfumed_Garden\" title=\"Perfumed Garden\">Perfumed Garden</a> before the boy revealed his true identity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Kindly_man\" title=\"Kindly man\">kindly man</a> offers to send <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_Black_and_White\" title=\"House of Black and White\">House of Black and White</a> to become a courtesan in <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>, but the girl refuses and chooses to remain with the <a href=\"/index.php/Faceless_Men\" title=\"Faceless Men\">Faceless Men</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Brusco\" title=\"Brusco\">Brusco</a> makes it plain to Cat of the Canals (a disguised Arya) that while selling her oysters, clams, and cockles she is never to speak to a courtesan unless spoken to first.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Cat tells crew from the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Brazen_Monkey\" title=\"Brazen Monkey\">Brazen Monkey</a></i> that she sold three cockles to <a href=\"/index.php/Bellegere_Otherys_(courtesan)\" title=\"Bellegere Otherys (courtesan)\">Bellegere Otherys</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Black_Pearl\" title=\"Black Pearl\">Black Pearl</a>, who called to Cat as she was stepping off her barge.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> As she pushes her barrow along the canals, Cat sometimes glimpses courtesans floating by on their way to evenings with some lovers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Dareon\" title=\"Dareon\">Dareon</a> deserts from the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> while in Braavos,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> preferring instead to write songs for the city's courtesans.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Arya learns that pretty young girls at the <a href=\"/index.php/Satin_Palace\" title=\"Satin Palace\">Satin Palace</a> dream of being courtesans.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Winds_of_Winter\"><i>The Winds of Winter</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Winds of Winter\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #f28500;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Content.png\" src=\"/images/c/cc/Content.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Warning</b> <br /> This information has thus far been released in a sample chapter for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i>, and might therefore not be in finalized form. Keep in mind that the content as described below is still subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Bellegere_Otherys_by_Lady_Rae.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/ad/Bellegere_Otherys_by_Lady_Rae.jpg/250px-Bellegere_Otherys_by_Lady_Rae.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"525\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/ad/Bellegere_Otherys_by_Lady_Rae.jpg/375px-Bellegere_Otherys_by_Lady_Rae.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/ad/Bellegere_Otherys_by_Lady_Rae.jpg/500px-Bellegere_Otherys_by_Lady_Rae.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Bellegere_Otherys_by_Lady_Rae.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Bellegere_Otherys_(courtesan)\" title=\"Bellegere Otherys (courtesan)\">Bellegere Otherys</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Black_Pearl\" title=\"Black Pearl\">Black Pearl</a>, by Rae Lavergne ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Famous courtesans attend a performance of <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Bloody_Hand\" title=\"The Bloody Hand\">The Bloody Hand</a></i> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Gate_(playhouse)\" title=\"Gate (playhouse)\">Gate</a>. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harys_Swyft\" title=\"Harys Swyft\">Harys Swyft</a> is accompanied by the <a href=\"/index.php/Bellegere_Otherys_(courtesan)\" title=\"Bellegere Otherys (courtesan)\">Black Pearl</a>, and three members of <a href=\"/index.php/Otharys\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Otharys\">Otharys</a> are each accompanied by a courtesan as well.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Mercy_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Mercy-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Famous_courtesans\">Famous courtesans</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Famous courtesans\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dd><b>Historical:</b></dd></dl>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Tyanna_of_the_Tower\" title=\"Tyanna of the Tower\">Tyanna of the Tower</a>, a mistress then wife of King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Johanna_Swann\" title=\"Johanna Swann\">Johanna Swann</a>, who became ruler of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a> in all but name as the Black Swan.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Bellenora_Otherys\" title=\"Bellenora Otherys\">Bellenora Otherys</a>, the second Black Pearl of Braavos, bastard daughter of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bellegere_Otherys\" title=\"Bellegere Otherys\">Bellegere Otherys</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Bellonara_Otherys\" title=\"Bellonara Otherys\">Bellonara Otherys</a>, a former Black Pearl and mother to the current one.</li></ul>\n<dl><dd><b>During <i>A Song of Ice and Fire:</i></b></dd></dl>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Bellegere_Otherys_(courtesan)\" title=\"Bellegere Otherys (courtesan)\">Bellegere Otherys</a>, the current Black Pearl.</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Veiled_Lady\" title=\"Veiled Lady\">Veiled Lady</a></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Merling_Queen\" title=\"Merling Queen\">Merling Queen</a></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Moonshadow\" title=\"Moonshadow\">Moonshadow</a></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Daughter_of_the_Dusk\" title=\"Daughter of the Dusk\">Daughter of the Dusk</a></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Nightingale\" title=\"Nightingale\">Nightingale</a></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Poetess\" title=\"Poetess\">Poetess</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lyseni</a> are also great breeders of <a href=\"/index.php/Slaves\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slaves\">slaves</a>, mating beauty with beauty in hopes of producing ever more refined and lovely courtesans and bedslaves.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters_-_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters_-_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>It must also be said that the courtesans of <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a> are renowned throughout <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">the world</a>, yet are all free women, unlike the more famous beauties of the <a href=\"/index.php/Pleasure_gardens\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pleasure gardens\">pleasure gardens</a> of Lys or the brothels of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>. Their art is not only for the bedchamber; their wit and their bearing make them much sought after by the richest merchants, the boldest captains, the most distinguished visitors. <a href=\"/index.php/Keyholders\" title=\"Keyholders\">Keyholders</a>, lords, and princes seek their favors. The most famous courtesans take poetic names that add to their allure and mystery.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Would you sooner be a courtesan, and have songs sung of your beauty? Speak the word, and we will send you to the <a href=\"/index.php/Bellegere_Otherys_(courtesan)\" title=\"Bellegere Otherys (courtesan)\">Black Pearl</a> or the <a href=\"/index.php/Daughter_of_the_Dusk\" title=\"Daughter of the Dusk\">Daughter of the Dusk</a>. You will sleep on <a href=\"/index.php/Rose\" title=\"Rose\">rose</a> petals and wear <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silken</a> skirts that rustle when you walk, and great <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> will beggar themselves for your maiden’s blood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Kindly_man\" title=\"Kindly man\">Kindly man</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The good folk of <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a> would soon be shuttering their windows and sliding bars across their doors. Night belonged to the <a href=\"/index.php/Bravo\" title=\"Bravo\">bravos</a> and the courtesans.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The courtesans of <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a> were famed across <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">the world</a>. Singers sang of them, <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">goldsmiths</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jewel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jewel\">jewelers</a> showered them with gifts, craftsmen begged for the honor of their custom, merchant princes paid royal ransoms to have them on their arms at balls and feasts and <a href=\"/index.php/Mummer\" title=\"Mummer\">mummers</a> shows, and <a href=\"/index.php/Bravos\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bravos\">bravos</a> slew each other in their names.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Courtesan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - The Voyage of Alyn Oakenfist.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_braavos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D